definitions: Fill a container or space tightly with something.
Fill the skin of a dead animal with material to restore its original shape, for display.
Fill food, especially poultry, with a mixture before cooking.
Forcefully push something into a space.
Eat a large amount of food.
examples: She began to stuff clothes into a bag.
The taxidermist will stuff the bird.
We'll stuff the turkey for Thanksgiving.
He stuffed the money into his pocket.
Don't stuff yourself with too much cake.
